e processAheadOfTime(MergedContextConfiguration mergedConfig,\n\t\t\tGenerationContext generationContext) throws TestContextAotException {\n\n\t\ttry (GenericApplicationContext gac = loadContextForAotProcessing(mergedConfig)) {\n\t\t\treturn this.aotGenerator.processAheadOfTime(gac, generationContext);\n\t\t}\n\t\tcatch (Throwable ex) {\n\t\t\tthrow new TestContextAotException(\"Failed to process test class [%s] for AOT\"\n\t\t\t\t\t.formatted(mergedConfig.getTestClass().getName()), ex);\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t/**\n\t * Load the {@code GenericApplicationContext} for the supplied merged context\n\t * configuration for AOT processing.\n\t * <p>Only supports {@link SmartContextLoader SmartContextLoaders} that\n\n[124 more lines in file. Use offset=330 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781026193802}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing AOT in Spring 7**\n\nI'm exploring the TestContextAotGenerator in Spring 7, particularly how it asserts the AOT TestContext during run-time execution. There’s an assertion failure that seems to come from existing merged context issues, especially regarding AOT processing and generated files. I'm thinking about the implications for features like CGLIB and how those settings might affect the AOT generator. The setup using @Bean methods could lead to some failures if configurations are missing. Additionally, there's a need to consider naming and static methods in this context.\n\n**Reviewing TestContextAotGenerator**\n\nI'm considering how TestContextAotGenerator.processAheadOfTime might utilize caching with a unique class, needing to reset before building. However, if another test has run on the same class, it could cause problems. I think it’s worth examining if making a @TestBean field package-private in a static nested test class is beneficial. I’m also curious whether the AOT generator could instantiate the context, especially regarding the BeanOverrideTestExecutionListener. It’s important to inspect the process to confirm if it invokes the post-processor correctly.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04fbef9b7139a29e016a284d772d908194b1a70e706c6c724e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKE2RluVzcZY3H5nFvkvVu24XZsbWQ-SwcYvci9Xm4kUa9qvJtkt-Tgl9SUhq6jrrQ-1JkDtsGwkswNo0uc55uJkrvThPeu3dtuHcxVLJwJqP_lvz-MEAJhN0JMpPSsYBv5KFBcoZulRGo7h5SquvO_7FM2hhrsSuGgUv0NLtvM_J5GrX8VffpguDH9QP5z9neiDTDE9dqQpmktqY95AnDAgNPurctkRcReCDjE0--d9V2fbC9T6C-SD34KnHHm4oZxMAaJhpSdkcB0_p20zZs2AJHjX-PDYlz_mx1C0upXM1WKonJuYIXlobnQOd4EYSKYk4Sy5d2hvGJhP4LyF72dAOcauEEoEdvLT9utEjI_jzsoOJQMUK4zYcSEIqwtFr97IwDmTsW-4sAb4k7mVn_KnU-bsx6dXP1pcqBDm2zb4N4gLWx8gSrUpKvinpl3QRYmOxmyeNei6uBORPlH_ivD67JioymqOwTiONYAdhMgUz8JO8veEeUTgWlUZOU5UOGAETtgJpIquCz-UOJTOn41